1 (b) (1) "Dwelling unit" has the same meaning as defined in K.S.A.
2 58-2543, and amendments thereto.
3 (2) "Tenant" has the same meaning as defined in K.S.A. 58-2543, and
4 amendments thereto An affiant who knowingly provides a false
5 affidavit to a law enforcement agency under this section may be
6 charged with a class A nonperson misdemeanor.
7 Sec. 3. (a) Upon receipt of the affidavit, the county sheriff applicable
8 law enforcement agency shall verify that the affiant is the record owner
9 of the dwelling unit or the authorized agent of the owner of the dwelling
10 unit and appears otherwise entitled to relief. Upon verification and after at
11 least 24 hours from receipt of the affidavit, the county sheriff a law
12 enforcement officer shall serve a notice on the unauthorized person to
13 vacate immediately the dwelling unit.
14 (b) Service may be accomplished by hand delivery of the notice to
15 any unauthorized person occupying the dwelling or by posting notice on
16 the front door or entrance of the dwelling unit. The county sheriff law
17 enforcement agency shall also attempt to verify the identities of all
18 persons occupying the dwelling and note the identities on the return of
19 service.
20 (c) The county sheriff law enforcement agency may arrest any
21 person found in the dwelling unit for trespass, burglary, theft, damage to
22 property or any other criminal act, or for an outstanding arrest warrant.
23 (d) The county sheriff law enforcement officer may charge a fee of
24 not more than $50 to process an affidavit filed pursuant to this act.
25 Sec. 4. (a) The affiant owner of the dwelling unit or the agent of the
26 owner of the dwelling unit shall provide notice at the dwelling unit
27 notifying the unauthorized person that such person has no right to occupy
28 the dwelling unit and must vacate immediately. The notice shall include
29 the street address of the county sheriff's office law enforcement agency
30 where the affidavit will be delivered. A copy of the notice with the date
31 and time of delivery shall be attached to the affidavit.
32 (b) An affiant who knowingly provides a false affidavit to the county
33 sheriff may be charged with a class A nonperson misdemeanor.
34 Sec. 5. No county sheriff's department law enforcement agency or
35 such agency's deputies or employees or political subdivision of the state
36 may be held liable for any action or omission made in good faith pursuant
37 to this act. A county sheriff's law enforcement officer is not liable to an
38 unauthorized person individual or any other party for loss, destruction or
39 damage of property.
40 Sec. 6. A person may bring a civil cause of action for wrongful
41 removal under this act against the affiant owner of the dwelling unit or
42 agent of the owner of the dwelling unit. An person harmed by a wrongful
43 removal under this act may have the possession of the dwelling unit

