1 restored and may recover actual costs and damages, as well as punitive
2 damages of triple the fair market rent of the dwelling, plus court costs and
3 reasonable attorney fees.
4 Sec. 7. (a) Sections 1 through 7, and amendments thereto, shall be
5 known as the removal of squatters act.
6 (b) As used in this act:
7 (1) "Dwelling unit" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 58-2543,
8 and amendments thereto, except that "dwelling unit" includes
9 commercial property and mobile homes.
10 (2) "Immediate family member" means spouse, child, grandchild
11 of any degree, parent, mother-in-law, father-in-law, grandparent of
12 any degree, brother, brother-in-law, sister, sister-in-law, half-brother,
13 half-sister, uncle, aunt, nephew or niece, whether biological, step or
14 adoptive.
15 (3) "Law enforcement agency" and "law enforcement officer"
16 mean the same as defined in K.S.A. 22-4606, and amendments thereto.
17 (4) "Squatter" means a person occupying a dwelling who is not
18 entitled to occupy the dwelling under a lease or rental agreement nor
19 authorized by a tenant to occupy the dwelling. "Squatter" does not include
20 a tenant who holds over in periodic tenancy.
21 (5) "Tenant" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 58-2543, and
22 amendments thereto.
23 (c) Occupancy by a squatter is excluded from the residential landlord
24 tenant act and the removal of a squatter shall not require the use of an
25 eviction action under such act.
26 Sec. 8. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
27 publication in the statute book.

